  "texts": [
    "The data collection involved cameras installed on vehicles and recorded sequences on highways in Madrid, Brussels, and Turin.",
    "The database includes 3,425 cropped rear-end images of vehicles taken from different angles and 3,900 images extracted from road sequences without vehicles.",
    "Images were selected to maximize the representativeness of the \"vehicle\" class and categorized into four regions based on the pose: center/near distance in front of the camera, left/near distance, right/near distance, and distant.These datasets serve as valuable resources for research and Development in various aspects of computer vision, particularly in the fields of object detection, tracking, and classification, especially as related to vehicles and traffic scenes.",
    "Evaluation MetricsAs mentioned earlier, we evaluated and compared different models on the provided public dataset.",
    "Metrics become particularly important when making comparisons."
